a:5:{s:5:"title";s:88:"Vendasta adds AI Optimization (AEO) to Snapshot Report to measure AI-answer visibility";s:16:"text-format-info";a:3:{s:10:"text-final";s:1879:"<p>Vendasta introduced a new AI Optimization (AEO) section inside Snapshot Report to help partners and businesses understand whether they’re being surfaced in AI-generated answers.</p>
<h3>What it does</h3>
<p>The AEO section provides a diagnostic view into:</p>
<ul>
<li>whether a site appears accessible to AI systems/crawlers, and</li>
<li>whether the business is mentioned in AI-style answer experiences (Vendasta cites Google AI Mode and ChatGPT).</li>
</ul>
<h3>What’s included</h3>
<p>Website audit: checks basic access signals (e. g., robots.txt and llm.txt where available).</p>
<p>Visibility audit: tests AI-style discovery across prompts/personas/engines using natural-language questions derived from keyword data; supports translated prompts and can show competitor visibility when applicable.<br />
Vendasta notes results are a standardized approximation because AI answers can change by context and over time.</p>
<h3>Who it’s for</h3>
<ul>
<li>Sales teams qualifying prospects and demonstrating competitive gaps</li>
<li>Businesses trying to understand how AI engines surface brands</li>
<li>Partners offering SEO and AI visibility services</li>
<li>Availability and setup</li>
</ul>
<p>Available for Snapshot Reports created after January 21, 2026.</p>
<p>If you use the default Snapshot Report template, it’s enabled automatically.</p>
<p>If your Snapshot Report is customized: Partner Center → Administration → Customize → Sales → Edit Default Snapshot Template → enable AI Optimization → Save.</p>
<p>If you use Markets, the section must also be enabled at the market level where applicable.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/new-ai-optimization-aeo-section-in-snapshot-report">https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/new-ai-optimization-aeo-section-in-snapshot-report</a></p>
